headline: The AI Power Trade Is Getting Tricky. Stocks to Consider in 2026.
summary: Electricity is a hot commodity, now that tech companies are paying a premium for it to power their artificial-intelligence data centers.  Utilities have ridden the trend to 23% returns in 2024 and 16% returns so far this year.  Most notably, politicians have grown concerned about increases in electricity rates and are already pressuring utilities to keep rates steady or even lower them.

headline: Is GE Vernova’s 102% Surge in 2025 Still Supported by Fundamentals?
summary: Wondering if GE Vernova is still a buy after its huge run up, or if you are already late to the party? This article is going to walk through the numbers behind the narrative. The stock has surged recently, jumping about 9.7% over the last week, 18.7% over the past month, and an eye catching 102.5% year to date with a roughly 109.5% gain over the last year, which naturally raises questions about how much upside might be left. These moves have come as investors refocus on the energy transition...

headline: GE Vernova price target raised to $840 from $735 at Goldman Sachs
summary: Goldman Sachs analyst Joe Ritchie raised the firm’s price target on GE Vernova (GEV) to $840 from $735 and keeps a Buy rating on the shares. The Power market appears to be at an early inflection point, with GE Vernova viewed as a leading way to gain exposure following a major upward revision to its 2028 targets, including $52B in revenue, a 20% adjusted EBITDA margin, and at least $22B of cumulative free cash flow from 2025-2028, the analyst tells investors in a research note.Claim 50% Off TipRa
